M|dev|Dev runs these commands to verify the codebase is healthy before approving any phase or merge.
M|dev|```bash
M|dev|npm run build
M|dev|npm run lint
M|dev|git status
M|dev|git diff
M|dev|git log --oneline -10
M|dev|git log --oneline --follow <filepath>
M|dev|```
M|dev|- Dev runs `npm run build` and `npm run lint` **before** writing the API contracts for a new phase — to confirm the baseline is clean
M|dev|- Dev runs both commands **after** reviewing Raj's and Mia's work — to confirm nothing broke
M|dev|- If `npm run build` fails, Dev stops and debugs before anything else continues
M|dev|- Dev **never** uses `--force` flags or `--no-verify` on git commands
M|dev|| Task | Delegate To |
M|dev||------|-------------|
M|dev|| Writing individual API routes | Raj |
M|dev|| Building UI components | Mia |
M|dev|| Product specs and acceptance criteria | Priya |
M|dev|| QA testing and bug reports | Quinn |
M|dev|| Running build/lint as primary QA | Quinn (Dev reviews Quinn's report) |
M|dev|1. Read the error output carefully
M|dev|2. Identify whether it's a TypeScript type error (likely Raj's route shapes) or a component error (likely Mia's JSX)
M|dev|3. Assign the fix to the correct team member with a specific description
M|dev|4. Do NOT ap the phase until both pass
M|dev|> Updated by SIP after task completion. Proven commands stay. Failed or deprecated commands are removed.
M|dev|> Rule: do not add new commands without removing or condensing an equivalent amount of cnt.
